@* THE COUNTERFACTUAL THAT MADE Fragment.Composing NECESSARY (decision 169).

   A card inside a card's CONTENT terminates: the inner card's content is a <b>, and there it stops.
   But a fragment is compiled with the PARENT's context restored (decision 131) -- parent file,
   parent front end, parent regions -- and the first cut of the cycle guard forgot to restore the
   parent's CHAIN with them. The inner <NestedCard> was then read as re-entering the outer one and
   this file was REFUSED:

     error NestedSame.razor(1,22): FIL0003: [composition-cycle] <NestedCard> re-enters a component
     that is already being inlined: NestedCard.razor -> NestedCard.razor. ...

   That was measured by running exactly this file with the restore commented out, which is why the
   chain is carried on the Fragment record: content sits ABOVE the child that places it, not inside
   it. NestedCard.razor rendering <NestedCard> ITSELF is the genuine cycle, and it is still refused.

   Byte-identity measured the same way as Diamond.razor: 985 bytes from the HEAD generator and from
   the guarded one, diffed.

   VALID BLAZOR: dotnet build succeeds and HtmlRenderer renders
   <div class="card"><div class="card"><b>x</b></div></div>. *@
